{
  "id": "dungeon-crawl",
  "name": "Dungeon Crawl",
  "dmNotes": "Template scene — rename it. Low drones and drip/echo ambience sell a dungeon better than music; keep the music sparse.",
  "music": [],
  "ambience": [],
  "sfx": [],
  "script": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Dungeon Crawl"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Your torchlight gutters against stone that has not felt wind in a hundred years. The passage ahead swallows the light after a dozen paces, and from somewhere below comes a slow, patient "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "drip... drip... drip",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "italic"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The air tastes of dust and old iron. Something down here is waiting to be found — or waiting for you."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Add a cave/dungeon ambience bed and a sparse exploration track from the library. Save a stinger SFX for the first trap or door — drop it as a "
            },
            {
              "type": "cue",
              "kind": "sfx",
              "ref": "...",
              "label": "🔊 ..."
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " cue right where you'll read it."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
